        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.5.19-21"/>
                <note type="curatorial">19</note>
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                
                <note type="authorial">
                    FIREPROOF
                    EUROPEAN PLAN
                    HOTEL KEYSTONE
                    K
                    POLAND &amp; MERRELL LESSES
                    McCOOK, NEBR.
                </note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        FRIDAY A.M.
                        Mch 14 '24
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dearest Ones:</salute>

                </opener>
                
                <p>I got here last night at 1:30 and slept until 8:30 this morning, so I'm feeling bully.</p>
                <p>There was no snow at Falls City, and the weather was spring -like- maple buds pretty well developed
                but some time from being out.</p> 
                <p>It snowed here last night and is snowing today - a thin warm snow, next thing to rain. I'll leave
                here tomorrow (Saturday) at 12:30 and reach Fairmont at 7:35. That is only 40 miles south of
                Osceola. ^Will read at Fairmont Sunday night in a church. All the churches will close I came over to
                hear the boat. Monday night I'll be at Osceola, &amp; I think I'll head for Omaha. Ralston on Tuesday
                night &amp; Council Bluffs Wednesday A.M. at 10:30 then I'll take the 4 P.M. Burlington.</p>
                <figure/>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.5.19-21"/>
                <note type="curatorial">20</note>
                <note type="authorial">-2-</note>
                
                <note type="authorial">
                    FIREPROOF
                    EUROPEAN PLAN
                    HOTEL KEYSTONE
                    K
                    POLAND &amp; MERRELL LESSES
                    McCOOK, NEBR.
                </note>
                
                <p>and reach Branson Thursday. &amp; It look slike something over 100 clean for this trip - not so bad.</p>
                <p>Might be considerably more, could easilt be 150.</p> 
                <p>I was talking to the editor of the Fall City Daily about the Julian and business, and he said that
                we've got 'em for infringement. A <unclear/> of a given work can be used legally - but not the
                whole. I do hope we can land for manages in excess of the minimum.</p>
                <p>I hope you are all feeling better by now &amp; that Mona got Mrs. Robertson.</p>
                <p>I have a strenuous time from now on - Sun, Mon, Tues, nights stright and Wed. morning. But I feel
                normal - not at all strained yet. Caught a cold on the way to K.C. there is no sleeper</p>
                <figure/>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.5.19-21"/>
                <note type="curatorial">20</note>
                <note type="authorial">-3-</note>
                
                <note type="authorial">
                    FIREPROOF
                    EUROPEAN PLAN
                    HOTEL KEYSTONE
                    K
                    POLAND &amp; MERRELL LESSES
                    McCOOK, NEBR.
                </note>
                
                <p>now; and the coach was draughty. But I doped up with <unclear/> &amp; the cold stopped. Slept in the
                hotel that first night - with Garner.</p>
                <p>I'm going to spend most of my time today at the University poetry contest. They sent me the 50 best
                poems recieved. 10,000 students to compete, and yet there's not a notable thing in the bunch! One
                little thing is good - a sort of Sara Teasdale lyric - short &amp; sweet. One pretentious poem is so
                bague I don't know what it's about. The others are almost nothing.</p>
                <figure/>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Lots of love to my six</salute> 
                    <signed>Jno</signed> 
                    <signed>Daddy.</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
